OL,3,GSouth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA cloudy start with patchy rain
OL,6,Fin places. Brightening up, with sunny
OL,7,Fspells but also the risk of showers
OL,8,Fdeveloping. These likely to be heavy,
OL,9,Fperhaps with thunder and hail,
OL,10,Fprimarily in the north of the region.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FShowers easing somewhat
OL,13,Fduring the evening but lingering for
OL,14,Fmuch of the night in places. Remaining
OL,15,Flargely cloudy and generally mild.
OL,16,
OL,17,CMonday:FA cloudy start for many on
OL,18,Fbank holiday Monday, with a few bright
OL,19,For sunny spells emerging. Further
OL,20,Fshowers are likely to bubble up during
OL,21,Fthe afternoon.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
